User: Can you show me some code examples for "Accessible Rich Internet Applications (ARIA)"?

Assistant: Here are some code examples:

### Progress Bar Markup
```yaml
<div
  id="percent-loaded"
  role="progressbar"
  aria-valuenow="75"
  aria-valuemin="0"
  aria-valuemax="100"></div>
```

### Dynamic ARIA Attributes Example
```yaml
// Find the progress bar <div> in the DOM.
const progressBar = document.getElementById("percent-loaded");

// Set its ARIA roles and states,
// so that assistive technologies know what kind of widget it is.
progressBar.setAttribute("role", "progressbar");
progressBar.setAttribute("aria-valuemin", 0);
progressBar.setAttribute("aria-valuemax", 100);

// Create a function that can be called at any time to update
// the value of the progress bar.
function updateProgress(percentComplete) {
  progressBar.setAttribute("aria-valuenow", percentComplete);
}
```

